1
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:24,440
The tow truck might be a little late.

2
00:01:24,800 --> 00:01:26,080
You've already said that twice.

3
00:01:28,120 --> 00:01:29,559
It's raining, and the roads are slippery.

4
00:01:29,879 --> 00:01:31,400
The tow truck will be delayed for a few hours.

5
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:34,239
You have a really good memory.

6
00:01:38,080 --> 00:01:39,120
Let me remind you.

7
00:01:39,639 --> 00:01:40,760
Don't force a conversation.

8
00:01:41,519 --> 00:01:42,400
If you do that,

9
00:01:42,879 --> 00:01:43,800
it'll just make things more awkward.

10
00:01:46,639 --> 00:01:47,160
I got it.

11
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:00,839
You're hungry.

12
00:02:04,959 --> 00:02:05,559
No, I'm not.

13
00:02:05,839 --> 00:02:06,519
You say you're not,

14
00:02:06,879 --> 00:02:07,800
but your stomach is growling.

15
00:02:20,479 --> 00:02:21,279
Well, fine.

16
00:02:21,679 --> 00:02:22,559
Let's just say I'm hungry.

17
00:02:23,279 --> 00:02:24,119
Do you want something to eat?

18
00:02:26,160 --> 00:02:28,119
How can you just say whatever comes to mind?

19
00:02:28,720 --> 00:02:29,960
Eat what? Thin air?

20
00:02:30,559 --> 00:02:31,440
Is there anything to eat here?

21
00:02:31,559 --> 00:02:32,559
Of course there is.

22
00:02:33,119 --> 00:02:33,880
Wait.

23
00:02:37,679 --> 00:02:39,520
Isn't this food?

24
00:02:40,639 --> 00:02:41,279
Look.

25
00:02:41,559 --> 00:02:42,759
Pastries.

26
00:02:44,440 --> 00:02:45,320
And there's wine, too.

27
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:47,600
Hurry up.

28
00:02:48,479 --> 00:02:48,880
Have some.

29
00:02:48,880 --> 00:02:50,279
You don't want to eat the offerings, do you?

30
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:51,919
Yeah.

31
00:02:52,479 --> 00:02:53,520
Haven't you heard?

32
00:02:54,119 --> 00:02:55,880
The offerings made to ancestors,

33
00:02:56,119 --> 00:02:57,880
eating them is like receiving a blessing.

34
00:03:05,839 --> 00:03:06,839
I thought you weren't going to eat.

35
00:03:08,399 --> 00:03:09,559
You're the one who told me to eat anyway.

36
00:03:10,039 --> 00:03:11,279
If Mom and Dad blame anyone,

37
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:12,800
they'll blame you.

38
00:03:14,919 --> 00:03:15,720
Okay.

39
00:03:15,720 --> 00:03:16,759
Then I'll have one, too.

40
00:03:21,199 --> 00:03:22,960
The Chairman's funeral just finished,

41
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:24,520
and they've already announced

42
00:03:24,520 --> 00:03:26,039
the layoff plan for Tongzhou Factory.

43
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:27,399
What kind of nonsense is this?

44
00:03:28,399 --> 00:03:29,759
Even if Rosenmoss

45
00:03:29,919 --> 00:03:31,199
is the largest creditor,

46
00:03:31,679 --> 00:03:33,199
Feimanchi hasn't gone bankrupt yet.

47
00:03:33,639 --> 00:03:34,919
They're going way too far with this.

48
00:03:34,919 --> 00:03:35,520
Zi'ang.

49
00:03:35,759 --> 00:03:36,360
No,

50
00:03:36,880 --> 00:03:37,399
Director Feng.

51
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:38,679
Don't you agree?

52
00:03:39,440 --> 00:03:40,160
Uncle,

53
00:03:40,479 --> 00:03:41,919
I need to explain this to you.

54
00:03:43,039 --> 00:03:45,360
Rosenmoss has clauses that restrict us.

55
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:46,639
The largest creditor

56
00:03:46,919 --> 00:03:47,880
is allowed to participate in management.

57
00:03:48,839 --> 00:03:49,679
Since Feimanchi

58
00:03:49,759 --> 00:03:51,199
is currently in an unstable phase,

59
00:03:51,880 --> 00:03:53,600
they definitely want to take this chance to interfere.

60
00:03:54,639 --> 00:03:55,600
Interferences like this

61
00:03:56,039 --> 00:03:57,080
will probably happen more often in the future.

62
00:03:58,080 --> 00:03:58,600
Then...

63
00:03:59,679 --> 00:04:00,119
Then...

64
00:04:00,399 --> 00:04:01,639
The only person we can trust now

65
00:04:01,919 --> 00:04:02,960
is you, Director Feng.

66
00:04:03,720 --> 00:04:04,639
Can you think of a way

67
00:04:04,839 --> 00:04:06,759
to withdraw Rosenmoss's layoff plan?

68
00:04:07,479 --> 00:04:08,039
I know.

69
00:04:08,679 --> 00:04:09,160
Rest assured.

70
00:04:10,039 --> 00:04:10,880
Next week, after I'm elected

71
00:04:10,880 --> 00:04:12,119
as the official CEO,

72
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:13,960
I'll discuss countermeasures with the directors.

73
00:04:18,760 --> 00:04:19,640
These past few days,

74
00:04:20,119 --> 00:04:21,440
why have you been hiding?

75
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:26,040
I suddenly felt a bit confused.

76
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:30,559
Maybe my uncle was right.

77
00:04:32,880 --> 00:04:35,160
I'm actually using the company as an excuse

78
00:04:36,959 --> 00:04:38,799
to do the exact same things he does.

79
00:04:53,799 --> 00:04:54,640
I know

80
00:04:58,040 --> 00:04:59,279
you feel sad, too.

81
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:03,600
The reason you've become so ruthless

82
00:05:05,559 --> 00:05:07,320
is because you're afraid of getting hurt.

83
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:09,119
Right?

84
00:05:15,279 --> 00:05:16,799
Why don't you choose

85
00:05:18,119 --> 00:05:19,440
to live the kind of life

86
00:05:20,839 --> 00:05:22,920
where you won't have any regrets?

87
00:06:15,559 --> 00:06:16,519
Gu Tiancheng,

88
00:06:17,880 --> 00:06:18,959
are you crazy?

89
00:06:59,359 --> 00:06:59,920
Director Feng.

90
00:07:00,239 --> 00:07:01,200
The Board of Directors

91
00:07:01,239 --> 00:07:02,559
is looking forward to meeting you.

92
00:07:02,959 --> 00:07:04,200
The labor union is also quiet.

93
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:06,679
Now, as long as the inauguration ceremony goes well,

94
00:07:06,880 --> 00:07:07,959
everything will be perfect.

95
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:09,559
Your election as President

96
00:07:09,880 --> 00:07:10,720
is truly

97
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:12,000
what everyone wants.

98
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:14,880
Old Hu,

99
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:15,799
you've worked hard too.

100
00:07:16,640 --> 00:07:18,160
It's all thanks to your guidance.

101
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:22,079
Hello, Director Feng.

102
00:07:23,799 --> 00:07:24,480
Secretary Lin.

103
00:07:25,079 --> 00:07:26,519
The drafts of the inaugural speech you submitted,

104
00:07:26,519 --> 00:07:27,359
I've already read them.

105
00:07:27,760 --> 00:07:28,679
The first one is very good.

106
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:30,359
Let's prepare based on the first draft.

107
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:31,559
Also,

108
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,399
please personally check

109
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:34,760
the press release materials for the media.

110
00:07:35,640 --> 00:07:36,359
I understand.

111
00:07:36,959 --> 00:07:38,440
I will contact the PR manager

112
00:07:38,640 --> 00:07:39,600
and carefully review the materials.

113
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:42,799
By the way,

114
00:07:45,440 --> 00:07:47,279
if I have to instruct you on every single thing like this,

115
00:07:47,880 --> 00:07:49,119
don't you think it's very inefficient?

116
00:07:51,119 --> 00:07:52,239
What do you mean?

117
00:07:52,839 --> 00:07:54,440
Please report back to the President's office immediately.

118
00:07:56,799 --> 00:07:58,320
But what about Mr. Gu? I...

119
00:07:58,720 --> 00:07:59,640
I'll talk to him.

120
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:04,720
Okay.

121
00:08:04,959 --> 00:08:05,640
I understand.

122
00:08:10,279 --> 00:08:11,720
Sorry, I'm late.

123
00:08:15,359 --> 00:08:16,440
Why did you want to meet here?

124
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:19,200
Because there's a very important occasion tomorrow.

125
00:08:19,640 --> 00:08:20,480
What important occasion?

126
00:08:20,920 --> 00:08:22,600
The President is coming to China tomorrow.

127
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,920
Why does the President suddenly want to come to China?

128
00:08:26,119 --> 00:08:29,079
The President wants to finalize the acquisition of Feimanchi.

129
00:08:29,239 --> 00:08:30,559
There are also other

130
00:08:30,559 --> 00:08:31,559
M&A cases to study in the country,

131
00:08:31,760 --> 00:08:32,760
so he came in person.

132
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:35,000
But the company hasn't gone bankrupt yet.

133
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:37,359
Why finalize the acquisition plan now?

134
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:40,760
It's going to go bankrupt sooner or later anyway.

135
00:08:41,599 --> 00:08:42,440
That's not important.

136
00:08:42,760 --> 00:08:44,440
What's important is that you know in two months,

137
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:45,919
the election for the new Vice President will begin.

138
00:08:46,799 --> 00:08:48,559
You are the strongest candidate.

139
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:51,280
So you must perform well tomorrow

140
00:08:51,520 --> 00:08:53,320
and leave a very good impression on the President.

141
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:55,000
Got it.

142
00:08:58,760 --> 00:09:00,280
These signature dishes seem pretty good.

143
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:01,280
I want to try them all.

144
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:02,960
Okay, whatever you say.

145
00:09:04,760 --> 00:09:05,400
Your coffee.

146
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:06,520
Thank you.

147
00:09:07,760 --> 00:09:09,520
The sale of Feimanchi,

148
00:09:09,880 --> 00:09:11,119
the President cares a lot about it.

149
00:09:13,719 --> 00:09:15,960
This company originally had good commercial value.

150
00:09:17,159 --> 00:09:18,840
It was just ruined by Gu Rongchen.

151
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:22,159
Anyway,

152
00:09:22,440 --> 00:09:23,840
all the interested parties,

153
00:09:24,520 --> 00:09:25,679
you have to personally take charge of them.

154
00:09:30,280 --> 00:09:31,159
Let me ask you something.

155
00:09:33,359 --> 00:09:34,320
Go ahead.

156
00:09:34,320 --> 00:09:35,840
Why are you acting so serious?

157
00:09:38,760 --> 00:09:39,520
If,

158
00:09:40,479 --> 00:09:41,359
I mean if,

159
00:09:43,799 --> 00:09:44,840
a woman you find ridiculous

160
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:47,039
and very annoying,

161
00:09:48,159 --> 00:09:49,280
and this woman,

162
00:09:50,479 --> 00:09:53,280
kissed you one day while drunk...

163
00:09:54,880 --> 00:09:57,320
This woman is not bad!

164
00:09:58,239 --> 00:09:58,880
What would you do?

165
00:09:59,880 --> 00:10:00,359
No,

166
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:02,239
the key is,

167
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:04,200
how do you feel about this woman?

168
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:05,239
Do you like her?

169
00:10:06,760 --> 00:10:07,960
Me?

170
00:10:09,640 --> 00:10:10,719
What do you mean how I feel about her?

171
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:11,919
Who said it was me?

172
00:10:11,919 --> 00:10:12,679
It's not me.

173
00:10:13,599 --> 00:10:14,520
Right, right, right.

174
00:10:15,159 --> 00:10:16,400
Not you, not you, not you.

175
00:10:16,559 --> 00:10:18,479
Then, then let's talk about that guy.

176
00:10:19,280 --> 00:10:20,440
That silly guy.

177
00:10:20,799 --> 00:10:21,840
Does he like this woman?

178
00:10:26,760 --> 00:10:27,640
Maybe

179
00:10:27,880 --> 00:10:28,599
a little bit.

180
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:29,640
That makes sense.

181
00:10:30,280 --> 00:10:30,880
What's wrong?

182
00:10:32,119 --> 00:10:33,000
That means...

183
00:10:34,479 --> 00:10:35,640
It proves that this woman

184
00:10:36,119 --> 00:10:36,880
hates you.

185
00:10:36,880 --> 00:10:37,719
Who said it was me?

186
00:10:38,039 --> 00:10:39,000
I told you it wasn't me.

187
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:39,400
Okay, okay, okay.

188
00:10:39,400 --> 00:10:40,479
It's not you, not you, not you.

189
00:10:40,840 --> 00:10:42,520
Definitely not you. Definitely not.

190
00:10:43,359 --> 00:10:44,080
Then how about this?

191
00:10:44,280 --> 00:10:44,880
Let's just say this...

192
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:45,520
This...

193
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:46,840
This guy,

194
00:10:47,159 --> 00:10:47,799
he...

195
00:10:48,359 --> 00:10:49,359
because he was drunk,

196
00:10:49,719 --> 00:10:50,679
kissed this girl.

197
00:10:51,080 --> 00:10:52,520
If he pesters her because of this,

198
00:10:52,919 --> 00:10:55,159
I think this gentleman's behavior is a bit...

199
00:10:56,359 --> 00:10:57,039
sleazy.

200
00:10:58,599 --> 00:10:59,359
Then what should he do?

201
00:11:00,479 --> 00:11:01,280
As for a solution,

202
00:11:01,280 --> 00:11:02,400
there is one.

203
00:11:02,880 --> 00:11:04,119
But tell me,

204
00:11:04,880 --> 00:11:06,200
who is this guy?

205
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:07,440
And who is this girl?

206
00:11:07,760 --> 00:11:08,479
Suit yourself.

207
00:11:09,280 --> 00:11:10,119
No, no, no.

208
00:11:10,239 --> 00:11:11,159
Okay, okay, okay.

209
00:11:11,239 --> 00:11:11,760
Fine.

210
00:11:12,919 --> 00:11:14,640
I know who it is even if you don't tell me.

211
00:11:18,359 --> 00:11:19,200
There's an old saying,

212
00:11:19,359 --> 00:11:20,159
"If a man isn't bad,

213
00:11:20,159 --> 00:11:20,919
women won't love him."

214
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:23,440
I've always been a bad man,

215
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:24,799
but nobody likes me.

216
00:11:25,280 --> 00:11:25,960
It's different.

217
00:11:27,559 --> 00:11:28,320
You're crazy.

218
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:30,239
A crazy man and a bad man

219
00:11:30,719 --> 00:11:31,719
are two different concepts.

220
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:34,760
Get lost.

221
00:11:35,880 --> 00:11:36,520
Jiaqi,

222
00:11:37,080 --> 00:11:38,080
take a look at this.

223
00:11:38,440 --> 00:11:39,200
What is this?

224
00:11:39,880 --> 00:11:41,359
This is Tongzhou Factory

225
00:11:41,679 --> 00:11:42,799
and Feimanchi Research Institute's

226
00:11:43,039 --> 00:11:45,239
jointly developed new product proposal.

227
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:47,039
Uncle wants to trouble you

228
00:11:47,320 --> 00:11:48,599
to show it to President Gu.

229
00:11:50,159 --> 00:11:51,280
Why show it to him?

230
00:11:51,640 --> 00:11:53,200
Did something happen at the factory?

231
00:11:56,200 --> 00:11:58,159
The layoff plan has been announced.

232
00:11:58,520 --> 00:11:59,799
The statutory notification period

233
00:12:00,119 --> 00:12:01,559
has been over for almost a month now.

234
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:03,400
We are really frustrated.

235
00:12:03,799 --> 00:12:04,640
Are we just going to

236
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:06,400
be kicked out like this?

237
00:12:07,880 --> 00:12:08,640
Zi'ang and I...

238
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:09,640
No,

239
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:10,719
I also talked to Director Feng.

240
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:13,159
The Board of Directors made nice promises,

241
00:12:13,559 --> 00:12:15,440
but it seems they haven't done much.

242
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:17,679
So I was thinking,

243
00:12:18,039 --> 00:12:19,119
the one who holds the decision-making power

244
00:12:19,559 --> 00:12:21,280
should still be Rosenmoss.

245
00:12:22,039 --> 00:12:22,760
Jiaqi,

246
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:24,320
What I gave you are all

247
00:12:25,359 --> 00:12:26,080
proposals with good prospects

248
00:12:26,080 --> 00:12:27,479
and great commercial value.

249
00:12:27,960 --> 00:12:29,200
As long as we are given a chance,

250
00:12:29,679 --> 00:12:30,559
we have the confidence

251
00:12:30,799 --> 00:12:31,640
to save the company.

252
00:12:32,320 --> 00:12:32,799
Right.

253
00:12:33,159 --> 00:12:33,799
Uncle,

254
00:12:34,280 --> 00:12:35,080
to be honest with you,

255
00:12:35,559 --> 00:12:37,080
their actual purpose of coming to the company

256
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:38,599
is to make the company go bankrupt

257
00:12:38,840 --> 00:12:39,640
and then sell it.

258
00:12:40,039 --> 00:12:41,599
That way they can make more money.

259
00:12:43,039 --> 00:12:44,080
This proposal

260
00:12:44,840 --> 00:12:45,840
probably won't be of much use.

261
00:12:47,119 --> 00:12:47,840
I know.

262
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,000
If it were someone else,

263
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:51,039
I wouldn't hold much hope either.

264
00:12:51,520 --> 00:12:52,239
But isn't this

265
00:12:52,239 --> 00:12:53,479
President Gu's father's company?

266
00:12:53,919 --> 00:12:55,520
And you are right by his side.

267
00:12:56,280 --> 00:12:57,799
So could you please do me a favor

268
00:12:58,080 --> 00:12:59,960
and ask President Gu to reconsider?

269
00:13:02,239 --> 00:13:02,719
Okay.

270
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:03,679
I understand.

271
00:13:04,119 --> 00:13:04,919
I will definitely deliver it.

272
00:13:49,119 --> 00:13:50,679
It seems he's not home today either.

273
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:52,359
Seriously.

274
00:13:52,799 --> 00:13:54,799
What happened last time was so awkward.

275
00:13:55,440 --> 00:13:56,919
How should I bring it up?

276
00:14:15,719 --> 00:14:16,599
You scared me to death.

277
00:14:18,280 --> 00:14:19,320
You're that easily scared?

278
00:14:19,599 --> 00:14:20,559
I can't believe that scared you.

279
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:23,239
If I stood behind you and scared you,

280
00:14:23,840 --> 00:14:24,919
you'd jump too.

281
00:14:26,799 --> 00:14:28,400
You came to see me today.

282
00:14:29,280 --> 00:14:30,880
Do you have something to say?

283
00:14:33,679 --> 00:14:34,359
Yes.

284
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:35,760
Are you free right now?

285
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:39,000
You need to act as cold as possible.

286
00:14:39,280 --> 00:14:40,080
Make her feel like

287
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:41,880
you don't care about the kiss at all.

288
00:14:42,280 --> 00:14:43,320
Wouldn't that make me a player?

289
00:14:43,760 --> 00:14:44,520
Exactly.

290
00:14:45,159 --> 00:14:45,719
A player.

291
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:46,880
Just be a player.

292
00:14:49,400 --> 00:14:50,039
Sure.

293
00:14:50,919 --> 00:14:52,119
I have something to say to you too.

294
00:14:52,880 --> 00:14:53,400
Come in.

295
00:14:59,200 --> 00:14:59,679
Come.

296
00:15:12,559 --> 00:15:13,159
That's right.

297
00:15:13,960 --> 00:15:14,840
Just like that.

298
00:15:15,520 --> 00:15:16,880
Be a little colder.

299
00:15:17,080 --> 00:15:19,200
As cold as possible.

300
00:15:20,880 --> 00:15:21,520
Have a seat.

301
00:15:23,239 --> 00:15:24,400
Pour yourself some water if you're thirsty.

302
00:15:24,520 --> 00:15:25,119
Okay.

303
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:38,840
Well,

304
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:45,039
let me speak first.

305
00:15:47,359 --> 00:15:48,000
Okay.

306
00:15:49,119 --> 00:15:50,159
This isn't how it should go.

307
00:15:51,159 --> 00:15:52,840
How is she even colder than me?

308
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:56,039
Take a look at this.

309
00:15:59,799 --> 00:16:00,719
What is this?

310
00:16:02,440 --> 00:16:03,599
This is the Tongzhou Factory

311
00:16:03,599 --> 00:16:05,280
and Feimanchi Chemical Research Institute's

312
00:16:05,559 --> 00:16:08,000
ongoing new product project proposal.

313
00:16:10,520 --> 00:16:11,760
Why are you showing me

314
00:16:12,440 --> 00:16:13,000
this?

315
00:16:13,320 --> 00:16:14,719
I hope you'll reconsider

316
00:16:15,440 --> 00:16:16,559
and give the company a chance.

317
00:16:17,400 --> 00:16:18,080
If you're willing...

318
00:16:18,080 --> 00:16:18,640
Wait a minute.

319
00:16:21,840 --> 00:16:24,320
You came all the way to see me today

320
00:16:25,280 --> 00:16:26,479
just to talk about this?

321
00:16:30,200 --> 00:16:30,880
Yes.

322
00:16:32,880 --> 00:16:33,559
So,

323
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:35,400
you have nothing else to say?

324
00:16:36,919 --> 00:16:37,640
No.

325
00:16:40,080 --> 00:16:41,520
Lin Jiaqi, I'm suddenly so

326
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:43,080
confused by you.

327
00:16:43,359 --> 00:16:44,119
You...

328
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:47,880
This is the first time we've met since that day.

329
00:16:49,080 --> 00:16:49,719
Are you...

330
00:16:49,919 --> 00:16:50,919
Are you really going to say nothing

331
00:16:50,919 --> 00:16:52,239
and just let this pass?

332
00:16:53,039 --> 00:16:53,919
About what happened that day,

333
00:16:55,640 --> 00:16:56,799
let's just forget it.

334
00:16:58,520 --> 00:16:59,520
Treat it as a misunderstanding.

335
00:17:00,239 --> 00:17:01,200
A misunderstanding?

336
00:17:02,559 --> 00:17:03,520
Wow, just wow.

337
00:17:03,520 --> 00:17:04,599
You're really something, Lin Jiaqi.

338
00:17:04,680 --> 00:17:05,640
You... You think

339
00:17:06,079 --> 00:17:06,880
a kiss

340
00:17:07,359 --> 00:17:08,199
is just a misunderstanding?

341
00:17:09,199 --> 00:17:10,560
Then in your daily life,

342
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:11,719
do you just casually have

343
00:17:11,719 --> 00:17:12,359
this kind of misunderstanding?

344
00:17:12,439 --> 00:17:13,280
What are you talking about?

345
00:17:16,800 --> 00:17:17,199
I...

346
00:17:17,199 --> 00:17:18,479
I took it very seriously,

347
00:17:19,199 --> 00:17:19,839
you know?

348
00:17:20,199 --> 00:17:20,800
After that day,

349
00:17:22,479 --> 00:17:23,319
I was nervous,

350
00:17:23,479 --> 00:17:24,040
I...

351
00:17:24,839 --> 00:17:25,760
I was anxious.

352
00:17:26,839 --> 00:17:28,520
That day meant something special to me.

353
00:17:30,680 --> 00:17:31,359
But

354
00:17:33,239 --> 00:17:34,680
you think it was a misunderstanding?

355
00:17:41,239 --> 00:17:42,000
I never thought...

356
00:17:43,280 --> 00:17:44,479
...you'd be so innocent.

357
00:17:47,880 --> 00:17:48,319
Me?

358
00:17:49,280 --> 00:17:50,400
Is it wrong for me to be innocent?

359
00:17:51,760 --> 00:17:52,199
I...

360
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:53,319
I actually thought...

361
00:17:53,640 --> 00:17:54,640
...you felt the same way I did.

362
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:56,199
That we were both on the same page.

363
00:17:57,239 --> 00:17:58,319
But I didn't expect you...

364
00:17:59,160 --> 00:17:59,920
You...

365
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:01,439
...to be so cold-hearted.

366
00:18:02,959 --> 00:18:03,439
Such a player.

367
00:18:03,640 --> 00:18:04,520
What are you talking about?

368
00:18:05,680 --> 00:18:07,160
I just didn't want it to affect our work.

369
00:18:07,719 --> 00:18:09,079
And I was afraid you'd feel uncomfortable.

370
00:18:09,359 --> 00:18:10,880
I think you're the one who feels uncomfortable.

371
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:12,839
That's why you didn't even want to mention it...

372
00:18:12,839 --> 00:18:13,880
...and just let the whole thing pass.

373
00:18:16,760 --> 00:18:17,439
Alright.

374
00:18:19,239 --> 00:18:19,880
Since...

375
00:18:20,479 --> 00:18:22,000
...you want to be strictly professional and talk about work,

376
00:18:23,560 --> 00:18:24,479
...these documents you brought me...

377
00:18:24,479 --> 00:18:25,280
...I won't even look at them.

378
00:18:28,239 --> 00:18:29,239
If you want to talk to me about work,

379
00:18:29,239 --> 00:18:29,920
...just leave.

380
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:31,439
I don't work at home.

381
00:18:32,599 --> 00:18:33,280
President Gu.

382
00:18:33,280 --> 00:18:34,599
I'm someone who works in M&A.

383
00:18:36,079 --> 00:18:36,719
Right.

384
00:18:37,640 --> 00:18:38,520
Fair enough.

385
00:18:39,599 --> 00:18:40,479
Then why did you still come?

386
00:18:44,280 --> 00:18:45,920
If it were before, I definitely wouldn't have come.

387
00:18:47,920 --> 00:18:49,400
But now I'm slowly realizing...

388
00:18:50,160 --> 00:18:51,319
...that you've been changing.

389
00:18:52,520 --> 00:18:54,479
You're not as cold and ruthless as you used to be.

390
00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:56,280
Besides,

391
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:57,680
I know...

392
00:18:58,119 --> 00:18:59,359
...you've been helping the Chairman.

393
00:19:00,439 --> 00:19:02,280
And that you feel regret for the things...

394
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:03,280
...you've done in the past.

395
00:19:04,439 --> 00:19:05,079
So,

396
00:19:06,119 --> 00:19:07,079
...I came here today.

397
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:08,560
So you want me to choose...

398
00:19:08,560 --> 00:19:09,560
...that so-called...

399
00:19:09,640 --> 00:19:11,560
...lifestyle of living with no regrets?

400
00:19:13,319 --> 00:19:14,560
Let's not talk about this anymore.

401
00:19:16,560 --> 00:19:17,599
I will help you.

402
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:22,319
No matter what happens,

403
00:19:24,160 --> 00:19:25,680
I won't let you feel confused anymore.

404
00:19:26,319 --> 00:19:27,400
Or feel afraid.

405
00:19:28,839 --> 00:19:30,199
I will stay by your side...

406
00:19:31,760 --> 00:19:32,640
...and help you.

407
00:19:45,079 --> 00:19:47,000
Tomorrow, the President of Rosenmoss

408
00:19:47,520 --> 00:19:48,599
is finally coming to China.

409
00:19:49,119 --> 00:19:49,719
Really?

410
00:19:50,400 --> 00:19:51,920
I can finally meet the President.

411
00:19:53,280 --> 00:19:54,400
Then I need to prepare well.

412
00:19:54,719 --> 00:19:55,560
But the problem is,

413
00:19:55,920 --> 00:19:57,520
the President's itinerary this time

414
00:19:58,199 --> 00:19:59,959
also includes going with the companies

415
00:20:00,680 --> 00:20:01,880
interested in the acquisition to the Tongzhou Factory

416
00:20:02,239 --> 00:20:03,199
for a site visit.

417
00:20:05,680 --> 00:20:06,479
As you know,

418
00:20:06,760 --> 00:20:08,079
the sale of the Tongzhou Factory

419
00:20:08,359 --> 00:20:09,359
is already a done deal.

420
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:11,680
Now we just need a good price

421
00:20:12,400 --> 00:20:13,239
and then we'll sell it off.

422
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:16,000
This factory...

423
00:20:16,800 --> 00:20:18,599
Didn't the factory go on strike today?

424
00:20:19,479 --> 00:20:20,359
A labor dispute

425
00:20:20,560 --> 00:20:22,040
will directly have a huge impact

426
00:20:22,040 --> 00:20:23,040
on the sale of Feimanchi.

427
00:20:23,880 --> 00:20:25,239
It could ruin the sale.

428
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:27,359
If this happens,

429
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:29,079
it will put us at a huge disadvantage.

430
00:20:32,040 --> 00:20:33,000
However,

431
00:20:33,880 --> 00:20:35,640
with Gu Tiancheng and the Rosenmoss Group

432
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:36,400
acting as our shields,

433
00:20:37,160 --> 00:20:38,479
we just need to maintain a neutral stance

434
00:20:38,640 --> 00:20:39,880
and manipulate things from behind the scenes.

435
00:20:40,479 --> 00:20:41,719
If anything happens,

436
00:20:42,400 --> 00:20:43,680
we'll just pin the blame on them.

437
00:20:45,800 --> 00:20:47,040
Understood, understood.

438
00:20:47,239 --> 00:20:49,079
Then I'll get to work on this right away.

439
00:20:59,000 --> 00:20:59,599
Morning.

440
00:21:00,520 --> 00:21:01,280
Morning, Jiaqi.

441
00:21:01,560 --> 00:21:02,359
Mr. Gu, you asked for me?

442
00:21:06,199 --> 00:21:07,079
Did you need something?

443
00:21:08,839 --> 00:21:10,160
You'll be working outside today.

444
00:21:11,319 --> 00:21:12,280
Okay, where to?

445
00:21:12,920 --> 00:21:13,880
To the Tongzhou Factory.

446
00:21:14,119 --> 00:21:15,119
Bring back the missing

447
00:21:15,119 --> 00:21:15,599
accounting documents.

448
00:21:16,520 --> 00:21:17,959
I was originally supposed to go,

449
00:21:17,959 --> 00:21:19,359
but the Chairman is coming today,

450
00:21:19,359 --> 00:21:20,839
so I can't make it.

451
00:21:21,079 --> 00:21:21,719
Sorry to trouble you.

452
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:23,199
It's fine.

453
00:21:25,119 --> 00:21:26,000
Um...

454
00:21:26,839 --> 00:21:28,199
Did you read the documents I gave you?

455
00:21:29,040 --> 00:21:30,800
Did you think I'd read them if you left them at my place?

456
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:33,119
I won't read them.

457
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:43,520
Is there anything else?

458
00:21:44,040 --> 00:21:45,839
You'd better go to the factory and return these things.

459
00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:47,560
Also,

460
00:21:47,800 --> 00:21:49,239
I want the documents

461
00:21:49,560 --> 00:21:50,439
on my desk before three o'clock.

462
00:21:53,280 --> 00:21:54,160
I got it.

463
00:21:55,479 --> 00:21:56,119
Let's go, Qi Shuai.

464
00:21:56,680 --> 00:21:57,199
Alright.

465
00:21:57,760 --> 00:21:58,280
Bye-bye.
